On Wednesday, August 09, 2006, at 06:38PM, Wayne <mga60(-at-)optonline.net> wrote:

>I have a '79 Bus and would like to know what type of clamps were originally
>used on our bus's FI fuel lines. were they screw clamps or, as I expect,
>crimp clamps?

There were fuel injection screw clamps on top of the engine and some crimp clamps below. I can't remember exactly where the crimp clamps were (Scott Lyons will know).

Either way, I recommend that you use the FI clamps everywhere because they make it easy to change the hoses later.

